This paper discusses a measure of problem hardness in optimization, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). It also involves the analysis of fitness landscapes, which is a topic in computational biology (cs.CE) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses mathematical reasoning to justify the behavior of the measure, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
